parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel filler neck can cause gasoline to spill out of the filler neck, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Gasoline spills out of the filler neck when refueling
even when pumping slowly; fuel gushes out of the tank after the pump handle clicks off; fuel leaks onto the ground and surrounding areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the vehicle can cause loss of control, leading to accidents and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
often without warning; the vehicle may stall when turning or braking; the steering becomes difficult or impossible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended engagement of the 4x4 system can cause loss of control, leading to accidents and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The 4x4 system engages by itself
causing the vehicle to lose traction and control; the 4x4 system engages even when not selected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
often while driving at low speeds or when turning
and may restart immediately or after a delay. No warning lights or error codes are displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system issues can cause fuel leaks, fires, and accidents, especially when driving or refueling.
symptoms: Fuel overflows when filling up
and the vehicle may stall or hesitate when driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leaks and burning smell can cause engine damage, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the engine
and a burning smell is present inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended shifting into 4-wheel drive can cause the vehicle to slow down suddenly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The 4-wheel drive light flashes
the vehicle shifts into 4-wheel drive or 4-low on its own
the wheels lock up
the vehicle slows down or stalls
and the transmission makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes unusual noises
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The differential failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The differential makes unusual noises
the vehicle leaks fluid
and the differential overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Filler Inlet Check Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank filler inlet check valve can cause fuel to spill out of the filler tube when the vehicle is being refueled, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially in the presence of an ignition source.
symptoms: Fuel spills out of the filler tube when refueling
fuel shoots back out of the filler tube
fuel gushes out of the filler tube when the tank is full
fuel leaks out of the filler tube
fuel splashes out of the filler tube and onto the person refueling
fuel spills onto the vehicle and ground.
